name: Silicon Vultures 7" EP BLACK
description: You heard it through the rapevine, oh blood sucking unicorns. From their frantic smart punk soundwaves to synthesized art trash mayhem, SILICON VULTURES circle the crystalline deserts in search of their prey. Born through a sickness for musical restrictions, especially within so-called punk, the SV spit in the face of narrow-minded pseudo-elitist clowns, with sassy vigour – a fusion of psychosexually drenched punk assaultage and pummelling no-wave rhythms, the SV only relish in the idea that a reaction negative or otherwise would just be another feather in their cap. The flow of sugar rush vocals and haywire screams spew out images of sarcastic post-modern nightmares, against a backdrop of guitar and synth based artery stabs, bass distortion bombs and neckswinging drum pummels. The time of your life? or seatbeltless at the wheel of an imminent car wreck? either way its a glorious fucking mess Full Tracklisting: 1. Incest Wounded Nun 2. Howling Stallion Teen Feast 3. Sour Tits 4. Born Heaven For The Vampire Set 5. D.U.T.F

name: Hassle Volume 1 CD (Features 'Sour Tits')
description:
Extensive and affordable taste of tasty modern hardcore’- Katie Parsons Kerrang/Radio 1

	The very first compilation on one of the best record labels in the world, ‘Hassle Volume 1’
 will be released on October 29th across the UK on Hassle Records, home to Alexisonfire,
The Zico Chain, Juliette and the Licks, Attack in Black, Thursday.

	Compiled and created by Radio 1 Rock Show DJ Daniel P Carter, with liner notes from the Rock Show’s Katie P, this compilation features the absolute cream of the current crop of punk and hardcore acts across the globe, including the most talked about band of 2007, Gallows. Other acts include Canadian heroes the Cancer Bats, rising UK stars The Ghost of a Thousand, the incredible Rolo Tomassi and probably the best punk band (and punk name) about at the minute, Fucked Up, whose last London show at The Old Blue Last will go down in London live music folklore for
many, many years!!!

	Full track listings:
1.       Cancer Bats – French Immersion
2.       Outcry Collective – New Franchise Mess
3.       Flood Of Red – Don’t Sleep, Swim!
4.       Hexes – Semaphore Kids
5.       Blackhole – Witches
6.       The Ghost Of A Thousand – Left For Dead
7.       Gallows – Come Friendly Bombs
8.       Rolo Tomassi – Curby
9.       Sanzen – Modus Operandi
10.    Untitled Musical Project – A Popular Musical Composition
11.    Silicon Vultures – Sour Tits
12.    1000 Hertz – Give Me An Amen!!
13.    The Fucking Hate – Indoor Scarfs
14.    Cry For Silence – A World Benign 
15.    Fucked Up – David Comes To Life
 
The compilation will be limited to 2000 copies!!!
